rComments: I absolutely love George! He is really easy to understand, and answers emails back within hours of emailing! best prof I have had in University, he motivates you to work hard and do well. Thanks to him, I now want to pursue a career is stats! He is also funny, the class is awesome and really interesting, the only bad part was it was at 8:30am!

He is one of those failed frat boys who is angry at the A students for making him look bad. I understand and know how to use stats; but all he cared about was the one button pressing error  out of 200. Anyone care to guess the probability of making a button pressing error on an exam? This is why real math profs care about the steps not the number.

Really nice guy and he's pretty funny. I think he thinks everyone is naturally good at stats though and i found the exams hard even with days and days of studying. Nice not having to buy a text book either!

If you follow any advice in your university career make it what im going to tell you. DROP THIS COURSE! worst mistake I ever did was take this course with him. I am a A student but got an E in his class. he single handedly ruined my chances at grad school!
He is a terrible prof. He sucks
i dropped his class b/c i cudnt stand him and his midterms!!! but jokes on me cuz i needed that close for my thesis....now im just praying that wen i actually take the class...it wont be him!
He is a really nice guy, but he makes stats concepts to abstract to understand. I would like to talk to this guy about an abstract topic, but for stats I won't take a class with  him again.

The worst teacher I've ever had. Projects require you to have extensive knowledge computer programs not taught during the course or in prerequisites. It is expected that you learn material that is not covered in the text or in class. Professor is an genuine jerk to deal with. Avoid him at all costs!

Seems like a nice guy but murders you on the exam. Teaches like we are all math grad students, but forgets that most people are just trying to pass. Don't bother emailing for help, responds with a 'your email did not keep my interest throughout...' His assignments come from left field, his text book reads like a car manual...DO NOT TAKE WITH HIM!!!

TERRIBLE prof.  At first he seems nice and approachable, but really he's not.  Assignments have nothing to do with course content/curriculum.  Tests are impossible.  Hard marker.  I suggest avoiding him at ALL costs. Horrible, horrible teacher..
He was "ok"...I imagine there could be worse professors...but sometimes it's just hard to pay attention to him...granted it was a stats. class
Very low key, humourous (dry) manner, but successfully puts those with stat/math phobias at ease. He is both motivated & motivating. In a word - outstanding.

Very good prof. Makes the material easy to understand and tests closely reflect what is being taught in his lectures. He is very approachable if you need any help and likes to get to know his students.

Great prof!  very witty and very dry sence of humour; halarious! he is very slow and meticulous when he teaches.  This allows you really understand and follow the course material.  would suggest him to anyone!

Wants to be funny,but you end up laughing at him rather than with him.Txt is online,written by him,goes off on tangents which confuse & annoy.Tests are hard, material not related to psy.Good class for math-inclined, but if you arent, he's unsuccessful at helping you understand it;you'll either do really well or almost fail -> take schindler instead
Great guy, great teacher. From what I've heard of other stats profs, I think he is the best!

Provided free text online which was easy to follow and filled with jokes and puns. Lecture slides were great and he somehow always manages to slip in anecdotes about his dogs and his facination with cycling into lectures. Tough exams but is always willing to help out during office hours. Got an okay mark, but would like to have him for stats II.
Great teacher. He is entertaining and always willing to help. He used a text that he wrote himself and posted it on the internet for us, so it was free!! Great guy.
Very clear and helpful!  Goes through the material slowly and thoroughly.  Class is a LOT of work though.
Very helpful, loves to teach, tough tests but you will have to learn, which is the point right? He has a great sense of humor, enjoy it because most Prof's don't.

Excellent teacher.  Moves through slowly enough and is always helpful.  It was a hard class, and I got a low mark, which means I'd usually not be happy with the teacher, so that just says how good he is.

Clear, explains things well - exams are a bit challenging, but very fair. Probably the best prof you could take stats with. He moves slow enough for everyone (sometimes frustratingly so). I wish I would have him again for the second half to stats!

Best prof you could have for stats. Very clear and helpful- will explain until you understand. Uses practical examples to illustrate the purpose of material. I am not good at math by any means and came out with an A-. Requires a LOT of work, but it pays off with this prof. If you have to take stats, take it with him.

He teaches things well, although his exams always prove to be a bit challenging, but fair. He is very approachable and always willing to help and generally moves slowly enough so that it's easy to follow along. An overall great prof.

George expects perfection from his students, which can be extremely difficult.Memorization is essential in his classes.Very intelligent man and an excellent prof.One of the best I have ever had, both interesting material, presentation, and direction.Study EXTREMELY well and you will excel!

The worst professor I have ever had. Who cares what the pole that went through Phineaus Gages head was made of...there are 30 more pages in the chapter...learn to teach what is important.  I have never worked so hard for a class and gotten such a bad mark....marks off for spelling...what the @#%^&*.  Should have given the class a refund.

this guy asks the most random questions on those weekly quizes.  you think you've studied everything about a particular topic and can still get screwed.  we had a section on lobotomies - he didn't ask about their use, the procedure involved or their importance - he asked the name of the tool used to perform them.  craziness!
